---
title: Get an access code or paper census
group: Census
version: 28.0.1
layout: census-website-respond/views/_master
---
{% block pageContent %}
   
    {% block main %}

        <div class="page__container container">

            {{
                onsBreadcrumb({
                    "ariaLabel": 'Breadcrumb',
                    "itemsList": [
                        {
                            "url": 'https://deploy-preview-157--census-website-respond.netlify.app/end-to-end/home/',
                            "text": 'Home'
                        },
                        {
                            "url": pageInfo.rootPath + '/help',
                            "text": 'Help with the census'
                        }
                    ]
                })
            }}

            <div class="grid">

                <div class="grid__col col-7@m">

                    <main class="page__main" id="main-content" role="main">

                        <h1 class="u-mb-l u-fs-xxl">Get an access code or paper census</h1>

                        <div class="page__body">
                            <p>To start your census online, you will need your access code printed on the invitation letter we sent you. Your 16-character access code will be a combination of letters and numbers.</p>

                            <img width="400" class="census-letter-thumb u-mb-m" src="{{pageInfo.rootPath}}/img/census-letter.svg" alt="Census 2021 invitation letter example showing location of access code" />

                            {% call onsPanel({
                                "type": "warn",
                                "classes": 'u-mb-m'
                            }) %}

                                Keep this code safe. You will need to enter it every time you access your census.

                            {% endcall %}

                            <h2>If you donâ€™t have an access code</h2>

                            <p>You can <a href="">request a new code</a> to start a new census if you have lost or not received an access code. This can be sent to you by text or post.</p>

                            <p>A new access code will start a new census, and you will lose any answers entered using a previous access code.</p>

                            {%
                                call onsCollapsible({
                                    "classes": 'u-mt-m',
                                    "id": 'collapsible-0',
                                    "title": 'Need to answer separately from your household?',
                                    "titleTag": 'h3',
                                    "button": {
                                        "close": 'Hide this',
                                        "contextSuffix": 'content',
                                        "attributes": {
                                            "aria-hidden": 'true'
                                        }
                                    }
                                })
                            %}

                                <p>If you need to answer separately from the people you live with, you can <a href="#">request an individual access code</a> to start a separate census.</p>

                                {% call onsPanel({
                                    "type": "warn",
                                    "classes": 'u-mb-m'
                                }) %}

                                    Someone in your household must still complete a census using a household access code

                                {% endcall %}

                            {% endcall %}

                            <h2>If you want to fill out a paper census</h2>

                            <p>You can <a href="">request a paper census questionnaire</a> to be sent in the post.</p>

                            <h3>Continuation questionnaire</h2>

                            <p>If you already have a paper questionnaire and there are more than 5 people in your household, you will need to <a href="#">request a continuation questionnaire</a>.</p>
                        </div>

                    </main>

                </div>

                <div class="grid__col col-4@m push-1@m u-mt-m">

                    {{-
                        onsRelatedLinks({
                            "id": 'related-links',
                            "title": 'Related content',
                            "itemsList": [
                                {
                                    "url": pageInfo.rootPath + '/help/how-to-answer-questions/paper',
                                    "text": 'Paper questions help'
                                },
                                {
                                    "url": pageInfo.rootPath + '/contact-us',
                                    "text": 'Contact us'
                                }
                            ]
                        })
                    }}

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
    
    {% endblock %}

{% endblock %}
